content:
Ask yourself, would you like to be the recipient if your life was on the line?  Then sign up and be willing to #bethematch it takes only a couple seconds, it does not hurt to swab and you won't die if you are asked to give stem cells or bone marrow, yet others we love cannot live without it. #Repost @fdny
"We owe him everything. It's hard to put into words how it feels," says Dawn Traynor, mother of 14-year old Kyle Richardson, who was diagnosed with Hodgkin‚Äôs Lymphoma in 2015, and who received a bone marrow transplant in March, 2016, using cells donated by FDNY Firefighter Robert Humphries. Today, Kyle and Firefighter Humphries met for the first time, at the 13th annual Honor Roll of Life ceremony held at #FDNY Headquarters in Brooklyn. Firefighter Humphries says, ‚ÄúThere was no hesitation. I would have done it no matter who it was. It‚Äôs a good feeling knowing that you can help.‚Äù To learn how you can make a difference in someone‚Äôs life, follow @NewYorkBloodCenter and visit www.bethematch.org

content:
You are inspiring and kind and üíØlegit! Proud to know you!  #Repost @loufemia (@get_repost)
„Éª„Éª„Éª
Haha Blowing up the news. Thank you to my great friend and one of the best people I know, Amy Freeze for letting me tell my story. Anyone who knows me knows I have been to hell and back...and now I couldn't be happier with how great I'm doing, my progress, outlook and where I am at with this journey. I've gotten countless messages telling me how I've inspired them to not give up when it got hard for whatever disease or experience they r dealing with. If I can repost this and one person is helped because of my story then it's all worth it to me. Be your own SUPERHERO in life. Cure MS. Motivate, inspire and spread good vibes... Start by doing what's necessary, then do what's possible; and suddenly you are doing the impossible. Make a difference...pay it forward , inspire and motivate. Do something bigger than yourself. I went from not walking to this. This was for a great charity, cause and ms awareness üëçüèªüí™üèªüí™üèªüí™üèªüí™üèª
#Multiplesclerosis, or #MS, is a long-lasting disease that can affect your brain, spinal cord, and the optic nerves in your eyes. It can cause problems with vision, balance, muscle control, and other basic body functions. MS happens when your immune system attacks a fatty material called myelin, which wraps around your nerve fibers to protect them. Without this outer shell, your nerves become damaged. Scar tissue may form. 
Never give up, push yourself and never let anyone tell u that u can't do something, ever!! They tell u that just because they can't do it themselves. Be strong and always have hope. Keep #family close, be active have positive energy and be stress free !!! Don't let it stop you....üôåüèªüëçüèªüëäüèª#inspiration#life#love#disease#ms#multiplesclerosis#fuckms#abc7ny#fitness#fitfam#tattoo#tattoos#ink#inked#tatted#instafit#nyc#usa#fit#fitlife#fitness#latergram#motivation#trendywendy#blessed#godbless#bjj üî•üî•üá∫üá∏ üá∫üá∏ üí™üèªüí™üèªüí™üèªüí™üèª#repost @amyfreeze @wendyshow @theellenshow  @abc7ny
